      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">30.201-1</ph> CAS applicability.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1898e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  See <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title41/html/USCODE-2018-title41-subtitleI-divsnB-chap15-sec1502.htm"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">48 CFR 9903.201-1</xref>. 
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1898e18" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  In accordance
with <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section1502&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 1502</xref>(b)(1)(B),
the threshold for determining the tentative applicability of CAS
at the contract level is the amount set forth in <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section2306a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2306a</xref>(a)(1)(A)(i),
as adjusted for inflation in accordance with <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section1908&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 1908</xref>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
